@node "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

  Copy
   JpegLibraryPrefs to SYS:Prefs
   JpegLibraryPrefs.info to SYS:Prefs

@endnode

@node "How_To_Use_It" "How to use it"

JpegLibraryPrefs is a preferences program for jpeg.library.

After running JpegLibraryPrefs, you can use the GUI to control specific
features of jpeg.library.

The slider adjusts how oftern the progress callback hooks are called during
image decompression.

When set to the extreme left, the indicator says 'App' which means that the
callbacks are controlled by the application.

When set to the extreme right, the indicator says 'Never' which means that
the callbacks are not called.

The percentage indicated otherwise indicates how often for the entire image
decompress the callbacks are called. For example if it is 20%, it will use
the callbacks 5 times during the decompression.

@endnode

@node "Compiler" "Compiler"
@{b}@{u}Compiler@{ub}@{uu}

JpegLibraryPrefs was written and compiled using CED V3.5 and SAS/C 6.58
on an Amiga 4000/060. Cyberguard was used to detect/correct programming
errors.

@endnode

